Description: Tune RemoteFX Progressive Cb/Cr quantization to cut chroma bleed
 ("coloured hue/residue") around high-contrast text. Upstream quantises the
 chroma vectors for the low/ultra-low connection tiers far coarser than luma
 (flat 0xAA / 0xBB, marked "tentative"), which rings colour around glyph edges.
 Replace them with graded vectors (finer at the low/mid DWT sub-bands) so
 broadband/WAN/modem clients get clean chroma. Luma is unchanged; the
 "standard" (LAN) table is already fine and left alone.
 .
 Scope: the GFX RemoteFX Progressive path (max_bpp=32, gfx.toml order=["RFX"]).
 Classic RFX (max_bpp=24) takes its quant from librfxcodec and is NOT affected
 by this file — that needs a separate librfxcodec patch.
 .
 Values are a tunable starting point: lower nibbles = finer chroma = sharper
 colour = more bandwidth. Raise back toward 0xAA/0xBB to trade quality for bytes.
 Sub-band order per byte/nibble: LH3 LL3, HH3 HL3, HL2 LH2, LH1 HH2, HH1 HL1.
Author: xrdp-fleet
Forwarded: not-needed
Last-Update: 2026-06-14
--- a/xrdp/xrdp_encoder.c
+++ b/xrdp/xrdp_encoder.c
@@ -72,5 +72,5 @@
 static const unsigned char g_rfx_quantization_values_lq[] =
 {
     0x66, 0x66, 0x77, 0x87, 0x98,
-    0xAA, 0xAA, 0xAA, 0xAA, 0xAA /* TODO: tentative value */
+    0x87, 0x88, 0x98, 0xA9, 0xAA /* fleet: finer Cb/Cr, less chroma bleed */
 };
@@ -79,5 +79,5 @@
 static const unsigned char g_rfx_quantization_values_ulq[] =
 {
     0x66, 0x66, 0x77, 0x87, 0x98,
-    0xBB, 0xBB, 0xBB, 0xBB, 0xBB /* TODO: tentative value */
+    0x98, 0x99, 0xA9, 0xAA, 0xBB /* fleet: finer Cb/Cr, less chroma bleed */
 };
